<topic id='dataset_paediatric_critical_care_minimum_data_set.overview'>
  <title>Overview</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>Data Set: Paediatric Critical Care Minimum Data Set - Overview</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>

  <p>
      <b>Introduction</b>
  </p>
  <p>
The 
    <xref outputclass="dataSet"
            keyref="dataset_paediatric_critical_care_minimum_data_set">Paediatric Critical Care Minimum Data Set</xref>
 (
    <xref outputclass="dataSet"
            keyref="dataset_paediatric_critical_care_minimum_data_set">PCCMDS</xref>
) provides a record of what happens to a 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 when they receive Paediatric Critical Care in a Paediatric Intensive Care Unit, or other critical care setting suitable for children.  </p>
  <p>
The primary purpose of the 
    <xref outputclass="dataSet"
            keyref="dataset_paediatric_critical_care_minimum_data_set">Paediatric Critical Care Minimum Data Set</xref>
 is to allow the operation of the 
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_definitions/national_tariff_payment_system.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">National_Tariff_Payment_System</xref>
 within paediatric critical care. The 
    <xref outputclass="dataSet"
            keyref="dataset_paediatric_critical_care_minimum_data_set">Paediatric Critical Care Minimum Data Set</xref>
 supports the 
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_definitions/national_tariff_payment_system.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">National_Tariff_Payment_System</xref>
 by capturing the data needed to generate a 
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_definitions/healthcare_resource_group.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">Healthcare_Resource_Group</xref>
 (
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_definitions/healthcare_resource_group.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">HRG</xref>
) for each calendar day (or part thereof) of a period of paediatric critical care; these 
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_definitions/healthcare_resource_group.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">Healthcare Resource Groups</xref>
 are then used to inform the annual aggregate costing exercise, NHS Reference Costs.  </p>
  <p>
      <b>Scope and Uses</b>
  </p>
  <p>
The scope of the 
    <xref outputclass="dataSet"
            keyref="dataset_paediatric_critical_care_minimum_data_set">Paediatric Critical Care Minimum Data Set</xref>
 is:  </p>
  <p>
a) All 
      <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENTS</xref>
 on a 
      <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_ward">WARD</xref>
 with a 
      <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_critical_care_unit_function">CRITICAL CARE UNIT FUNCTION</xref>
 of National Code 
      <i>'04 - Paediatric Intensive Care Unit (Paediatric critical care patients predominate)'</i>
  </p>
  <p>
b) All 
      <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENTS</xref>
 on a 
      <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_ward">WARD</xref>
 with a 
      <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_critical_care_unit_function">CRITICAL CARE UNIT FUNCTION</xref>
 of National Code of either:  </p>
  <ul>
      <li>
         <i>16 - Ward for children and young people</i>
      </li>
      <li>
         <i>17 - High Dependency Unit for children and young people</i>
      </li>
      <li>
         <i>18 - Renal Unit for children and young people</i>
      </li>
      <li>
         <i>19 - Burns Unit for children and young people</i>
      </li>
      <li>
         <i>92 - Non standard location using the operating department for children and young people</i>
      </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
to whom one or more of the following 
      <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_critical_care_activity_code">CRITICAL CARE ACTIVITY CODES</xref>
 applies for a period greater than 4 hours:
      <i> </i>
  </p>
  <simpletable outputclass="simpletable table table-striped table-sm">
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>04</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>
Exchange Transfusion (
                  <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 received exchange transfusion)        </p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>05</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>
Peritoneal dialysis (acute 
                  <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENTS</xref>
 only i.e. excluding chronic) *        </p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>06</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>
Continuous infusion of inotrope, pulmonary vasodilator or prostaglandin (
                  <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 received a continuous infusion of an inotrope, vasodilator (includes pulmonary vasodilators) or prostaglandin)        </p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>09</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                  keyref="business_definition_oxygen_therapy">Oxygen Therapy</xref>
            <p>
(supplementary 
                  <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                     keyref="business_definition_oxygen_therapy">Oxygen Therapy</xref>
, irrespective of ventilatory state) **        </p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>13</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>
Tracheostomy cared for by nursing staff (
                  <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 receiving care of tracheostomy cared for by nursing staff not by an external 
                  <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_carer">Carer</xref>
 (e.g. parent))        </p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>16</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>
Haemofiltration (
                  <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 received Haemofiltration)        </p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>50</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>Continuous electrocardiogram monitoring</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>51</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>Invasive ventilation via endotracheal tube</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>52</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>Invasive ventilation via tracheostomy tube</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>53</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>Non-invasive ventilatory support</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>55</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>Nasopharyngeal airway</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>56</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>Advanced ventilatory support (Jet or Oscillatory ventilation)</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>57</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>Upper airway obstruction requiring nebulised Epinephrine/ Adrenaline</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>58</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>Apnoea requiring intervention</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>59</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>Acute severe asthma requiring intravenous bronchodilator therapy or continuous nebuliser</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>60</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>Arterial line monitoring</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>61</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>Cardiac pacing via an external box (pacing wires or external pads or oesophageal pacing)</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>62</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>Central venous pressure monitoring</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>63</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>Bolus intravenous fluids (&gt; 80 ml/kg/day) in addition to maintenance intravenous fluids</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>64</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>Cardio-pulmonary resuscitation (CPR)</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>65</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>Extracorporeal membrane oxygenation (ECMO) or Ventricular Assist Device (VAD) or aortic balloon pump</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>66</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>
Haemodialysis (acute 
                  <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENTS</xref>
 only i.e. excluding chronic)        </p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>67</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>Plasma filtration or Plasma exchange</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>68</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>ICP-intracranial pressure monitoring</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>69</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>Intraventricular catheter or external ventricular drain</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>70</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>Diabetic ketoacidosis (DKA) requiring continuous infusion of insulin</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>71</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>Intravenous infusion of thrombolytic agent (limited to tissue plasminogen activator [tPA] and streptokinase)</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>72</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>Extracorporeal liver support using Molecular Absorbent Liver Recirculating System (MARS)</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>73</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>Continuous pulse oximetry</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>74</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
            <p>nursed in single occupancy cubicle</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>80</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>
Heated Humidified High Flow Therapy (HHHFT) (
                  <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 receiving HHHFT)        </p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>85</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
            <p> has an epidural catheter in situ</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>94</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
            <p> has arrhythmia requiring intravenous anti-arrhythmic therapy</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>95</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
            <p> has reduced conscious level (Glasgow Coma Score 12 or below) and hourly (or more frequent) Glasgow Coma Score monitoring</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>96</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>
Intravenous infusion of sedative agent (
                  <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 receiving continuous intravenous infusion of sedative agent)        </p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>97</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
            <p> has status epilepticus requiring treatment with continuous intravenous infusion</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
  </simpletable>
  <p>Notes:</p>
  <ul>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>
* National Code 05 applies as an inclusion criterion for acute 
                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENTS</xref>
 only: it does not apply with chronic 
                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENTS</xref>
.        </p>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>
** National Code 09 applies as an inclusion criterion when the 
                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 receives supplementary 
                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                     keyref="business_definition_oxygen_therapy">Oxygen Therapy</xref>
, irrespective of their ventilatory state.        </p>
         </div>
      </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
This data is captured and recorded locally and may be used for the purposes of direct care, clinical audit, Reference Costs, and other local uses. Any transmission of the 
    <xref outputclass="dataSet"
            keyref="dataset_paediatric_critical_care_minimum_data_set">Paediatric Critical Care Minimum Data Set</xref>
 must be covered by fair processing arrangements in accordance with information governance criteria and appropriate local arrangements.  </p>
  <p>
      <b>Commissioning Data Set</b>
      <b>Transmission</b>
  </p>
  <p>
Subject to the 
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/data_dictionary/messages/message_documentation/xml_schema_constraints/commissioning_data_set_version_6-2_xml_schema_constraints.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">Commissioning_Data_Set_Version_6-2_XML_Schema_Constraints</xref>
, the 
    <xref outputclass="dataSet"
            keyref="dataset_paediatric_critical_care_minimum_data_set">Paediatric Critical Care Minimum Data Set</xref>
 is sent to the 
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_definitions/secondary_uses_service.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">Secondary_Uses_Service</xref>
 (
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_definitions/secondary_uses_service.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">SUS</xref>
) as a part of the following Commissioning Data Set messages, 
    <xref href="https://digital.nhs.uk/data-and-information/information-standards/information-standards-and-data-collections-including-extractions/publications-and-notifications/standards-and-collections/scci0076-paediatric-critical-care-minimum-data-set-version-2"
            scope="external"
            format="html">SCCI0076</xref>
:  </p>
  <ul>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref outputclass="dataSet"
                  keyref="dataset_cds_v6-2_type_120_-_admitted_patient_care_-_finished_birth_episode_cds">CDS V6-2 Type 120 - Admitted Patient Care - Finished Birth Episode Commissioning Data Set</xref>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref outputclass="dataSet"
                  keyref="dataset_cds_v6-2_type_130_-_admitted_patient_care_-_finished_general_episode_cds">CDS V6-2 Type 130 - Admitted Patient Care - Finished General Episode Commissioning Data Set</xref>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/data_dictionary/messages/cds_v6-2/data_sets/cds_v6-2_type_140_-_admitted_patient_care_-_finished_delivery_episode_cds.asp"
                  scope="external"
                  format="html">CDS V6-2 Type 140 - Admitted Patient Care - Finished Delivery Episode Commissioning Data Set</xref>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref outputclass="dataSet"
                  keyref="dataset_cds_v6-2_type_180_-_admitted_patient_care_-_unfinished_birth_episode_cds">CDS V6-2 Type 180 - Admitted Patient Care - Unfinished Birth Episode Commissioning Data Set</xref>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref outputclass="dataSet"
                  keyref="dataset_cds_v6-2_type_190_-_admitted_patient_care_-_unfinished_general_episode_cds">CDS V6-2 Type 190 - Admitted Patient Care - Unfinished General Episode Commissioning Data Set</xref>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/data_dictionary/messages/cds_v6-2/data_sets/cds_v6-2_type_200_-_admitted_patient_care_-_unfinished_delivery_episode_cds.asp"
                  scope="external"
                  format="html">CDS V6-2 Type 200 - Admitted Patient Care - Unfinished Delivery Episode Commissioning Data Set</xref>
